race.comment: LOST HIS BEANS (1) grows a leg for rider Maloney who has two wins from as many steers and will strip fitter second-up from the spell. Trust that Vandyke has him cherry-ripe for this and should be right there when the whips are cracking. DISNEY CASTLE (2) has a handy record over this course and distance with a win and a placing from three attempts. Will be rock-hard fit for this and must be respected out of the champion Waller yard. Rates a leading contender. Former Victorian ZAMBEZI KHAN (4) resumes here for the new stable but has tuned up for this with two recent trials. Monitor market moves. TEXAS FIREBALL (5) is yet to miss a drum in three starts over this seven-furlong journey and can run a big race while fresh. WIREWALKER (10) is a last-start winner who shouldn't be slept on.
